Now Nikki Knows: this app helps you figure out what’s good for you so you can buy healthier/ cleaner options. *THIS IS NOT A PAID AD, I JUST HONESTLY THINK IT’LL HELP US ALL BE HEALTHIER*

Also, you can download it for free so it’s worth a shot!

I was most shocked about how bad my skincare products were. I used to use brands that advertise as being good for your skin but it turns out there’s a lot@of harmful additives in them, some that affect fertility. 😳

I also was shocked about snacks that I thought were healthy but weren’t as good for me as I thought. But one thing to note when scanning food items, don’t just look at the 0-100 scale, the app flags foods that are too caloric or fatty but sometimes they can be good fats, like with nuts. Mostly keep an eye out for the “additives” and see if there’s harmful additives in your food. 

#nownikkiknows #appreccomendation #healthylifestyle #healthyshopping

Now Nikki Knows: Argentinian culture, drinks, and money tips that I’ve learned while being here in ARGENTINA! 🇦🇷

I am so grateful for the opportunity to work on a project that brought me to Buenos Aires for the first time so I could not only DO what I love, but in a new place where I could learn about a new culture, meet new people, and experience a once in a lifetime thing— being in Argentina when they won the World Cup! What an unforgettable experience. 🤗

 #worldcup #argentinianculture #buenosaires #argentinianmate #moneytips #moneyexchange

What an experience of a lifetime— to just so happen to be filming in Argentina when they won the World Cup! I’ve never seen so many people unite in celebration like that. It was beautiful… and WILD! 🤪🇦🇷

This was also the first time since pandemic that I’ve travel to a foreign country (other than Mexico) and it reminded me how much I love meeting new people, learning about new cultures and customs, and trying new foods. 

I feel very grateful we made it out of that locked down time. The world is so beautiful and if we are lucky enough to get to see outside of our bubbles, it would be treasures missed not to try.
Happy Holidays from the Shamos Family! ♥️💚

It felt so magical with all the lights and decorations, the colorful buildings and cobblestone roads, mariachi music playing through the night, the nicest people and the best churros I’ve ever had in my life. Now Nikki Knows: how to save money flying to Mexico using the Cross Border Xpress! This hack was life changing and saved us so much money I had to share. 

We were trying to get to San Miguel de Allende for our friends’ wedding but when I looked at tickets a couple months before they were over $1000/per ticket to go from LAX to SMA!! It was insane! But my husband thought of the idea of driving to San Diego and flying out of Tijuana instead (so we were then flying domestically rather than internationally) and we found that the process was SOOOO easy to cross the border and fly out of TIJ because the airport sits right on the boarder of CA/Mexico and the Cross Border Xpress let’s you park on the CA, USA side and literally walk across a bridge straight into the TIJ, Mexico airport. 

It was so easy and so efficient and saved us so much money so I hope this video explains how to do it and you can save money too if you end up in a similar predicament!
#savemoney #moneyhacks #travelhacks #flyingtomexico #traveltips #crossborderxpress

To punish or to love? 🤯 I used to workout to punish, critique, judge, and or hate on my body… I spent most of my teenage and young adult years living this way… and no matter how thin or “in shape” I looked… I always felt insecure and never felt “good enough” 🙈🥹 

But my whole life, and even all my relationships…seem to change once I started learning how to love and accept myself just the way I was… 

I started to move my body (aka workout) from a place of deep love, gratitude, and appreciation for all that my body did for me on a daily basis. (IMPORTANT: this was a journey for me, it did not happen overnight, and it took a lot of courageous deep inner work to get to this place) 

Things I realized on my healing journey: 
👉No matter what your body looks like…. 
The gift of having a body…  is literally one of the greatest gifts of all time. 

But it’s on loan… 
One day you won’t have a body anymore. 
So don’t take it for granted. 

It’s one of the greatest pieces of technology that exists. 

The more you take care and love-on your body… the more it will take care of you. 

➡️ Find ways to move, workout, and or train in ways that light you up… that give you energy and enthusiasm for life rather than deplete you. 

Find ways to “move more” with friends. 

Some of my favorite magical memories in life are ones exactly like this… where I’m moving out in nature with friends…. Where I feel so alive and so lit up ✨

Ask questions and share ideas below 👇 

Hope this helps 💙

Tag friends you wanna move more with, and create more magical memories together ❤️ @nikkisoohoo 

Ps we’re announcing the WINNER TO OUR BIG GIVEAWAY soon! Thanks to everyone’s help we we’re able to raise over $1500 dollars to help save animals in need @animalloverescue @landsinlove_tierrasenamor ✨💙🙏

Now Nikki Knows:  As an actor, I know what it’s like to be super critical about my appearance. We’re always being judged and having to strive for the “perfect” body. But as I moved into my 30s I realized trying to be so perfect was super damaging to my body mentally and physically.
 
I used to try to just NOT eat if I thought I was getting too chubby. But that was so unhealthy.
 
I’m so grateful to have learned from my friends in health and fitness and places like @srw_labs who’ve taught me healthier ways to be the best version of myself. I know that I can focus on eating healthy whole foods, getting my body moving for at least 30 mins a day, and taking high quality supplements and vitamins like Msc¹ Tone which helps optimize my body for ketosis so I can burn more fat, control my appetite, and maintain muscle mass. I’ve learned from SRW the key to shine from the outside, is to look after what we put inside our bodies, at a cellular health level.
 
So now, I just strive to be the HEALTHIEST I can be, not the most Barbie-doll perfect.
 
#Tear2Tone #EmbraceYourBody #Msc¹Tone #SRWlabs #ToneFromWithin #ShapeFromWithin

Now Nikki Knows: what to do if you want to go on a trip but you are afraid you’re going to miss out on a job opportunity! — get Travel Insurance ✅

Traveling as an actor is easy as ever! With ~95% of auditions over self tape or via zoom, you can basically be anywhere in the world and be an actor. Live your life, do your thing, bring your self tape set up wherever you go and do your auditions from the road. 

👉 See my “Traveling Self Tape Set Up” for a list of equipment I bring with me when I travel. On my blog: www.nikkisoohoo.com/blog

AND THEN, when you GET a job, just be prepared to fly home or wherever your job is shooting (travel insurance also covers trip interruption!) 

All insurance needs for you to get your money back is a notarized letter. 

FUN FACT: I’m a Mobile Notary! ✍️

So hit me up if you end up in this situation and need someone to come to set to help you get your letter signed! 😜

Sometimes… life just turns out better than anything you could’ve imagined for yourself. 🤗

I always figured I’d honeymoon on the beach of Bora Bora, but instead we ended up in this adorable, romantic ski town in the French Alps. 

I didn’t even know how to ski before I met my husband. (This is my 3rd season skiing). And getting to adventure in a new place and do an activity we love to do together was a great experience. It challenged us, helped us grow, and brought us closer together— from being stuck at the bottom of a lift in thunder snow getting drenched, to figuring out which bus was going to get us where we needed to go, to spending quite nights playing card games and cuddling… it was almost like being in an escape room with your favorite person. So whether we were solving problems, having fun, or just exploring and enjoying the experience together… it was a good time. 💕

Thank you @eshamos for being the best adventure partner. For taking care of me when I was sick. For guiding us where to go. For always keeping good spirits no matter what is going on. And for always holding all our heavy luggage and ski gear every place we go. I’m so grateful for you. I love you hubby. Happy honeymoon!

#honeymoon #chamonixmontblanc #france🇫🇷 #skiseason #nikkiandeli #frenchalps

Now Nikki Knows: How to save money while traveling in Chamonix, France 🇫🇷 💰 

Here are a few “good to knows” that I learned during my honeymoon here:
🚌 Buses are cheap, easy, & efficient (especially since taxis are hard to get and there’s no Uber)
💳 Most places take credit card so no need to exchange a lot of money beforehand
💷 Choose to pay in local currency when you travel because you’ll likely get the better rate.

Us women can (in most cases) choose to be mothers… but not ALL women choose to be the kind of mom MY mom was/is. 

The kind who prioritizes her kids… who showed up (and still shows up) to every game, performance, birthday, graduation…anything that matters to us…

The kind who supports her kids’ decisions whether she agrees with them or not— who allows them to live their lives how they please and is just grateful for the time they want to share with her. 

The kind that still makes (or pays for) your meal when they see you because it’s one of the ways she likes to show you she cares. 

The kind that thinks of all the little ways to make your life easier or for you to feel special— She got ME a gift on Mother’s Day and I’m just a dog mommy 😂

I am so grateful to have a mother, who makes me feel loved, supported, seen, heard and cared for… who provides me with guidance, perspective, and also space to grow into the person I want to be. Who loves me unconditionally with all her heart. I feel it. I recognize how lucky and blessed I am to have you as my mom. Thank you for choosing to love me in the way you do. Happy Mother’s Day Mama 💕I love you 

Also, thank you for loving @rokkopom like a grandson. He feels so loved by you too. You’re a great Nini as well 🐶💕

We laughed together, cried together, and shared an unforgettable experience together. We cannot even begin to express the amount of gratitude and love we feel for our friends and family 🥰💕 This was one of the best weekends EVER celebrating our baby boy on the way! 

From the beautiful shower that my family and @_.stephanie.joy._ threw for me to the Beach Bash with our community, we had friends who came in from all over (Hong Kong, Vancouver, Oregon, & Vegas) to share in this special moment of our lives.

It’s amazing what our bodies can do. And to be honest, it’s been kind of challenging to accept my new body. I’ve cried some nights realizing I’m not as strong or capable as I used to be. Seeing the strained veins in my legs because they aren’t used to holding up so much weight… not being able to fit into some shoes or even wear my wedding ring because my hands and feet are so puffy… getting a new pimple on my face everyday (it feels like)… being out of breath just walking up a flight of stairs and feeling disappointed in myself for not going to the gym because the most I feel like doing is going for a walk…

My mind understands I’m making a baby and that’s a miracle and it’s doing so much… but my emotions sometimes have a hard time accepting it. 

I actually considered not even doing this shoot because I tried on all the maternity dresses that I see women wear in their photos and I just felt like an ugly, overweight elephant. It was devastating and demoralizing. But in the end I had some friends help me pick out some outfits I felt OK in and now that I see some of these photos, I’m really really grateful we did them. 

@hildabphotography did a great job and now I’ll always be able to look back on the days when my body did something amazing and smile because I’m proud of my body and what it can do. And there’s not likely many more times in my life I’ll look like this or experience this so I’m grateful to have captured this beautiful chapter of my life. 💕

We’ve had quite a busy last nine months. Traveled to Mexico, to Costa Rica, to France TWICE, to Italy, to Switzerland, to Kentucky, to Utah, to Colorado, to Oklahoma, to Maine, to Massachusetts— for work, for the Cannes Film Festival, for philanthropy to raise money for a charity, for our belated honeymoon, for a few ski trips, for visiting our friends and family… it was a pretty epic year! All while being pregnant. 🤪

And of course when our schedules were finally open to do a Babymoon, the doctor said I’m no longer allowed to go on a boat or a plane and that I should stay relatively close to home. 😑 

At first I was bummed, until I realized that we live in such a cool place and could just do a “staycation” —and plan a weekend of fun, relaxing events to do together, just the two of us. 🥰

We ended up going about an hour south of where we live and staying in a super cool, unique boutique hotel @lacasahotellb. Neither @eshamos or I had spent much time in Laguna Beach so it was really fun to explore the town together. We just acted like tourists and treated ourselves to luxurious experiences that we both love— fancy dinners, massages every other day, the Royal treatment pedicures… 💆🏻‍♀️💁🏻‍♀️

It was such a great getaway. Exactly what we needed before our lives change forever!!! Thank you @xpcalhounx for making our stay down in Laguna so enjoyable! And thank you @weaudition for setting up such a special treat for all of us Cannes Ones to Watch. Feeling so grateful 🥹💕

Jett is 2 months old today and I stepped on the scale to find that I’m right back to my pre-pregnancy weight. It’s been interesting hearing so many people tell me that I don’t look like I just had a baby— that I look so good… that I lost it all so fast. 

I’m not sure how to feel exactly because I honestly didn’t DO anything (intentionally, to lose weight). I haven’t walked further than down the street more than a hand full of times since I gave birth. I haven’t worked out. I don’t eat differently. Some may say it’s genetics. Some may say it’s because I’m breastfeeding. But all I know is that I am grateful to be “small” again because I actually had a lot of anxiety about not “bouncing back” quickly. 

If you are a mom or know a mom who didn’t pull the same cards as me, please have some grace for her. Being a first time mom (or just a mom in general) is hard. I just realized it’s 2:30p and I still haven’t brushed my teeth yet. I’ve been thrown up on 4 times (hence the pic of me not wearing clothes). And peed on twice. I only have one arm free pretty much all day because the baby wants to be held all the time. The house can never stay clean. There’s stuff all over the place no matter how many times I try to clean up. I can’t imagine the pressure and stress I’d feel if I also didn’t feel good about how my body looked. 

Maybe no one really had the expectation for me to lose it all quickly but hearing words like “I’m sure you’ll bounce back quickly” “You were so active before you’ll be fine” “Just get back on your routine of eating well and working out and you don’t have to worry” still made me feel pressure to do it quickly— thinking that I’d seem lazy or something for not getting on it. 

And yes, maybe some women do work really hard right out the gate to get back to where they were and should be given praise for their dedication and effort, but I just want every woman to feel like whatever they choose to do is right. Whether they are spending their time workout out or spending their time trying to figure out how to survive and keep others alive… you’re doing it. Be proud. It’s hard. You got it. You’re beautiful. 💕 #jetthudson

My ability to get things done in a timely manner has somewhat dwindled since becoming a mom… so here’s a slightly delayed 2023 recap post 🤪 

This was honestly one of the best years of my life. I got to spend my time and energy doing what I love, where I love, with people I love. I got to travel the world, work on so many fun projects, spend a lot of time with my family and friends, and best of all— My dream of starting a family and becoming a mom came true. 

I feel so blessed for this life I live. Literally I have everything I ever really wanted… so I guess 2024 is going to be about creating new dreams for me and my family, and just being as present as possible through Jett’s first year in this world, and just continuing to be grateful for all that I have. 🥰

Also, it’s my year— Year of the Dragon 🐉 😜 Let’s GOOOO!! 🙌

A day in the life of Jett… 😍

I can’t believe how fast (and slow) the time has gone by… Jett is now 3 months old. His smiles and laughs make my heart feel so full. He’s quite the chatter box and loves when mommy and daddy dance and sing with him. He’s one drooly cuddle bug whom is not the biggest fan of binkies but does love trying to get his whole fist in his mouth. 

As everyone has been discussing New Year’s resolutions and intentions for this year I decided to make mine about being PRESENT and really enjoying motherhood and watching Jett grow. From 0-1 yr there are so many changes and everyone tells us to cherish this moment… so that is exactly what I’ll do! 

I’m going to practice relaxing a bit and not being too overly work/career driven. I’m going to remind myself not to be so eager for Jett to get to the next phase of development and just appreciate and embrace the stage he’s currently at. I’m going to put down my phone more and play. I’m going to enjoy the greatest PRESENT I’ve ever been given 🥰
